    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hi, i'm trying to help my dad with some estate planning stuff and i'm a bit confused. can u explain what a \"durable power of attorney\" is? also how is it different from just a regular power of attorney? thanks",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A durable power of attorney is a legal document that grants someone the authority to make financial and property decisions on your behalf even after you become mentally incapacitated. This is different from a regular (or non-durable) power of attorney, which automatically ends once you are declared unable to manage your affairs. Because it remains in effect during incapacity, it is a crucial tool for protecting your assets without needing a court-appointed guardian later.",
      "source": "target",
